15:06.365 --> 15:08.825
He stole my look and gave it to himself!

15:08.825 --> 15:10.994
‐ Let's give our panelists a hand.

15:10.994 --> 15:13.580
‐ [audience applauding]
‐ I'll see you in hell.

15:13.580 --> 15:15.707
‐ [chuckling]
Not if I get there first.

15:15.707 --> 15:17.209
‐ Oh, I’ll be there first,

15:17.209 --> 15:18.961
and I’ll be waiting
with a platter of crudités.

15:18.961 --> 15:22.214
‐ I’ll bring my friend Satan,
because he and I will have already bonded

15:22.214 --> 15:24.675
while we were waiting
for your stinky‐ass to show up.

15:29.638 --> 15:33.851
‐ Oof, I gotta boil my fists after that.
‐ Gross.

15:33.851 --> 15:36.979
‐How’s it going out here?
‐ Well, I’m down to the “ate his dad” guy

15:36.979 --> 15:39.439
and the “mistress‐drowning
grandma embezzler.”

15:39.439 --> 15:44.444
I'm pretty sure he ate his dad on purpose,
but the evidence was all circumstantial.

15:44.444 --> 15:46.905
Chuckster is open and shut.
‐ Pffft. Come on!

15:46.905 --> 15:50.075
You could throw a dart in here and hit
someone who deserves to be executed.

15:50.075 --> 15:51.743
‐ No one <i>deserves</i> it.

15:51.743 --> 15:56.039
But, as much as it pains me,
I think I gotta choose the Chuckster.

15:57.332 --> 15:59.459
Or do I?
‐ Eh. Good luck with that.

15:59.459 --> 16:01.336
Gotta go be a human strap‐on.

16:02.171 --> 16:03.422
‐ [zipper unzips]
‐ [man screams]

16:03.422 --> 16:05.966
[audience laughing]

16:06.842 --> 16:11.471
‐ [chuckles] The most important thing
at an execution:

16:11.471 --> 16:14.099
don’t lose your head!

16:14.099 --> 16:15.434
[audience laughing]

16:15.434 --> 16:19.646
It's hard to get ahead nowadays!
[Bungles laughing]

16:19.646 --> 16:21.356
‐ You suck, Bungles!

16:21.356 --> 16:23.192
‐ Who me?

16:23.192 --> 16:25.861
‐ [audience cheering]
‐ Boooo!

16:25.861 --> 16:28.322
‐ It’s Dick Scab Guy from the web!

16:28.322 --> 16:30.741
‐ [audience laughing]
‐ [fanfare]

16:30.741 --> 16:33.911
‐ The time has come for justice!

16:33.911 --> 16:36.330
[audience cheering]

16:36.330 --> 16:40.083
‐ The time has come
for a favorable impression of the King

16:40.083 --> 16:42.920
in all future public opinion surveys!

16:42.920 --> 16:46.131
[audience murmuring]

16:46.131 --> 16:51.136
‐ And stick around as one lucky fan
plays the Halftime Scholarship Challenge!

16:51.136 --> 16:53.931
[audience cheering]

16:53.931 --> 16:57.935
‐ Now, bring out the condemned!

16:57.935 --> 17:00.521
Chuckster the Huckster!
‐ [audience cheering]

17:00.521 --> 17:04.816
‐ Come on, that's bullshit!
‐ Ho‐ho! Of course it's a man!

17:04.816 --> 17:07.694
‐ Chuckster the Huckster?
I’ve never even heard of this guy!

17:07.694 --> 17:11.448
‐ If it couldn’t be me,
I wish it was you dying up there.

17:11.448 --> 17:13.659
‐ Oh, thanks, sis.
That means a lot.

17:13.659 --> 17:15.994
[audience cheering]

17:17.120 --> 17:21.124
‐ I’m sworn to protect the realm,
and that includes convicts, too.

17:21.124 --> 17:22.918
Hope this is the right piece.

17:23.794 --> 17:26.588
‐ Sabotage?
I didn’t think you had it in you.

17:26.588 --> 17:31.051
‐ Prisoners are human beings.
Even awful ones like Charles Reinhold.

17:31.051 --> 17:33.303
This murder‐tainment is gross.

17:33.303 --> 17:38.725
If we kill people for our amusement,
then who are we to judge Reinhold?

17:38.725 --> 17:40.769
‐ Maybe I didn’t give you
a fair shake, Patrick.

17:40.769 --> 17:42.521
Your heart's in the right place.

17:42.521 --> 17:45.649
I mean, I wish you were dead
instead of everyone I loved,

17:45.649 --> 17:47.484
but you're an okay dude.

17:47.484 --> 17:51.697
AUDIENCE: [chanting] Death ma‐chine!
Death ma‐chine! Death ma‐chine!

17:51.697 --> 17:55.617
‐ I feel a poll rising!
‐ In your pants? Heh.

17:57.244 --> 17:59.997
‐ Never step on my punchlines.

17:59.997 --> 18:02.124
[audience cheering]

18:05.919 --> 18:09.548
Charles Reinhold,
AKA Chuckster the Huckster,

18:09.548 --> 18:12.968
you are hereby sentenced to death.
Any last words?

18:12.968 --> 18:15.304
‐ Quite a few. For you see...

18:15.304 --> 18:19.349
I’m not “Charles Reinhold.”
I'm...

18:19.349 --> 18:21.393
‐ [audience gasping]
‐ Robin Hood?!

18:21.393 --> 18:22.686
‐ That's right!

18:22.686 --> 18:25.731
The real Charles Reinhold
drowned on his gold yacht!

18:25.731 --> 18:29.735
I took his place to infiltrate the castle,
and here I am!

18:29.735 --> 18:32.070
‐ Thief! Thief!
He stole my look!

18:32.070 --> 18:35.824
‐ Once again, King Merriman,
I have ruined your evil schemes.

18:35.824 --> 18:39.203
Anyone can see this was a stunt
to win the favor of the people.

18:39.203 --> 18:41.914
Try feeding the poor and fixing the roads.

18:41.914 --> 18:44.082
‐ But that’s expensive!
And boring!

18:44.082 --> 18:47.127
‐ People don’t like stunts.
They like results.

18:47.127 --> 18:51.423
And that’s why everyone
needs to look under their chairs!

18:51.423 --> 18:53.926
‐ [audience cheering]
‐ They’re full of gold coins!

18:53.926 --> 18:56.553
WOMAN 1: Don't kill Robin Hood!
MAN: Robin Hood for president!

18:56.553 --> 18:57.679
WOMAN 2:
Fuck me, Robin Hood!

18:57.679 --> 18:59.431
‐ Goddammit, they’re turning on me!

18:59.431 --> 19:01.433
‐Little John! Let’s bounce!

19:03.143 --> 19:06.647
‐ He seems really popular.
‐ He did win fair and square.

19:09.024 --> 19:11.610
‐ Oh, dear. Arrrgh!
[grunts]

19:11.610 --> 19:14.571
[screaming, crying out]

19:19.201 --> 19:20.536
‐ [screams]
CORAL / RUBEN: Ahhh!

19:20.536 --> 19:22.412
‐ Fuck! That could've been one of us!

19:22.412 --> 19:24.873
‐ In hindsight,
who cares about stupid awards?

19:24.873 --> 19:26.750
[audience screaming]

19:26.750 --> 19:29.503
‐ Cheer, people!
Cheer, for God’s sake!

19:29.503 --> 19:33.173
It’s an execution!
It’s supposed to be fun!

19:33.173 --> 19:35.926
[screaming continues]

19:40.472 --> 19:43.475
‐ [relieved sighing]
Oh, thank Christ.

19:43.475 --> 19:46.103
‐ What's happening?!
‐ I did it! I saved him!

19:46.103 --> 19:47.688
[creaking]

19:48.397 --> 19:50.732
‐ Little John! Anybody!

19:51.900 --> 19:53.485
‐ The mercy bolt!
It's gone!

19:53.485 --> 19:54.778
‐ "Mercy bolt"?

19:56.446 --> 19:59.575
‐ [coughing, gagging]
Oh, God! This is so much worse!

19:59.575 --> 20:01.285
I can taste the blade!

20:01.285 --> 20:03.787
‐ Who would design a machine like this?!

20:03.787 --> 20:05.122
‐ Ack!

20:07.916 --> 20:09.042
[audience shrieks]

20:12.129 --> 20:13.463
‐ [gasps]

20:13.463 --> 20:16.300
‐ Patrick, is this a bad time to confess

20:16.300 --> 20:20.220
that Sgt. Meghan didn’t find
that fairy field by accident?

20:20.220 --> 20:23.432
I traded her the lives
of my fellow fairies for opium.

20:23.432 --> 20:25.350
‐ What?!
‐ [gasps, grunts]

20:25.350 --> 20:26.935
‐ [metal clanging]
‐ [audience booing]

20:26.935 --> 20:28.937
WOMAN:
Get a loan like the rest of us!

20:28.937 --> 20:30.564
‐ Feels good to get it off my‐‐

20:31.315 --> 20:32.900
[audience gasps]

20:32.900 --> 20:37.446
‐ This could not have gone worse.
‐ It went about how I expected.

20:37.446 --> 20:41.783
‐ What kind of monster built that thing?
The King is a madman!

20:41.783 --> 20:43.368
WOMAN 1:
What if he puts us in the machine?

20:43.368 --> 20:44.953
WOMAN 2:
I think I love the king now!

20:44.953 --> 20:47.206
MAN 1:
I now approve of our psychopathic king!

20:47.206 --> 20:49.666
MAN 2:
We’re 100% loyal, your grace!

20:49.666 --> 20:53.253
‐ You know, Your Majesty, some say
it is better to be feared than loved.

20:53.253 --> 20:55.547
‐ Y’know what?
I’ll take that W.

20:55.547 --> 20:57.049
Patrick‐‐

20:57.049 --> 20:59.009
‐ I'm sorry!
Please don't put me in the machine!

20:59.009 --> 21:02.221
‐ Ha! You’re hilarious.
We crushed it today!

21:02.221 --> 21:03.138
‐ We did?

21:03.138 --> 21:06.642
‐ Nobody’s gonna mess with a king
that puréed a folk hero!

21:06.642 --> 21:09.561
‐ This job’s not as black and white
as I thought.

21:09.561 --> 21:13.273
Did I help the kingdom or commit murder?

21:15.108 --> 21:17.945
‐ [as Robin Hood] <i>“Cheer up, Patrick!</i>
<i>You did a good job!</i>

21:17.945 --> 21:20.197
<i>Here, you win a free hat!”</i>

21:21.865 --> 21:23.116
‐ Thanks.

21:25.911 --> 21:29.915
‐ This was the worst day of my life.
‐ [man groaning]

21:29.915 --> 21:31.208
What happened?!

21:31.208 --> 21:34.127
‐ Naked Lady Island was shit!

21:34.127 --> 21:37.214
‐ Today’s lesson:
if you let your guard down for a second,

21:37.214 --> 21:41.176
you end up like Barry.
‐ Barry? We lost Barry?!

21:41.176 --> 21:43.178
‐ I mean, we didn't really lose him.

21:44.179 --> 21:46.181
♪

21:47.891 --> 21:51.478
‐ Does anyone want to switch bunks?
Barry’s creepin' me out.

21:51.478 --> 21:54.356
TOBEY:
Oh, stop asking! Just go to sleep!

21:57.693 --> 21:59.403
‐ Patrick, you should've seen her!

21:59.403 --> 22:02.823
Snakes for hair
and built like a brick shit house.

22:02.823 --> 22:04.658
I’m gonna marry that woman.

22:04.658 --> 22:06.702
‐ Jesus Christ, go to sleep.

22:09.580 --> 22:13.292
‐ [Broth moaning, grunting]
‐ Oh, my fucking God!

22:16.920 --> 22:18.755
I think I hate being a squire.

22:18.755 --> 22:22.968
BROTH: Patrick, do me a favor
and hiss like a snake for me.

22:22.968 --> 22:25.262
♪

22:56.043 --> 22:58.128
CHILD:
<i>That was amazing!</i>
